cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of characterizing the decode-forward region for multi-source, multi-relay, all-cast channels with independent input distributions. This problem falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of flow decomposition to describe the messages decoded and forwarded by each node, which is a topic in computer networks (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of imposing causal restrictions on the relays, which is a topic in control theory (cs.CC) and multimedia systems (cs.MM).
